> Want to master the art of cooking steak? Always remember high heat, room temperature meat, and lots of salt and pepper. Want to master the art of dinner? Never forget the show-stopping sides! Juicy, pan-seared sirloin is topped with an easy caramelized onion pan sauce and paired with toasty garlic bread and roasted carrots. To make things even more delicious, it's all served with the world's greatest condiment: horseradish cream sauce. It's tangy and punchy--the perfect cool contrast. This magical sauce goes well with everything on the plate, so don't be surprised when you find yourself swiping up every last drop.

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Trim and peel @carrots{3}, then slice into ½-inch-thick pieces on a
diagonal. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, scallion whites,
@horseradish powder{1/2%teaspoon}, and @water{1%tablespoon}. Season with
@salt{}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, microwave @butter{3%tablespoon} until
softened, about ~{10%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon} and a
pinch of @salt{}. Halve @demi-baguette{2}, then toast in a #toaster{} or
#toaster oven{} until lightly browned. Spread garlic butter onto toasts,
then cut each half on a diagonal.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, about ~{20%minutes}.

Pat @sirloin steak{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan
over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes}
per side. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Let rest at least
~{5%minutes} before serving.

Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat.
Add onion, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until
softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and
@water{2%tablespoon}; simmer for ~{1%minute}. Turn off heat. Stir in
@butter{1%tablespoon}. Divide steak, carrots, and garlic bread between plates.
Top steak with onion. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with horseradish
cream on the side.